{
  "stem": "19895.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the fate of the Jews was that they either planned on taking them out to a concentration camp and extermination camp locations, or-- or to blow up and then finish up everybody who is alive there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And life wasn't easy there because food was very scarce.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Disease in the ghetto was rampant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And many people will die, even so if they lived under as confined area of the city.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But for about six weeks or so, there were just decimated by death and disease, because there was no medical help.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Older people, basic medical needs were not available and so on, except some Jewish physicians who were trying their best for whatever supplies they could have.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were having some contact with the outside world.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And bribe and money somehow sometime let some medical supplies in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I am not the one to tell about Ghetto life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "All what I know about is what my father told me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we didn't know still anything about my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I found my grandmother to be alive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I found my mother's sister in the city who were alive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandmother, well, on the papers you asked me to fill out, we had to give the maiden names.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, maiden name was Rosa Friedmann.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And her married name was Schleyer, like my mother's maiden name and some of the names I mentioned.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and I do know for a fact that Viktor Schleyer, my mother's brother, his wife, his two daughters, and the older daughter's child, her husband, were all taken to Auschwitz-- never made it.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I do have cousins.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
